The paper proposes a method for video segmentation based on natural language queries, which involves both computer vision and natural language processing. Therefore, it is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) and natural language processing (cs.CL) sub-categories. The proposed method also involves the use of capsules, which are a type of neural network architecture, and attention mechanisms, which are commonly used in machine learning. Therefore, it is also likely to belong to the machine learning (cs.LG) and multimedia (cs.MM) sub-categories. Finally, the paper involves the use of deep learning techniques for video segmentation, which is a common application of artificial intelligence (cs.AI).
